Additional requirements for applications for public procurement are excluded by law
The legislation may lay down exhaustive requirements for applications for participation in procurement.
In the autumn session of the plenary session, the State Duma plans to consider in the second reading the draft law, which establishes the requirements for the content and composition of the application for participation in the procurement, which can only be participants of small and medium-sized businesses.
Amendments are made by the government to the law "On the purchase of goods, works, services by individual types of legal entities".
The draft law was developed in accordance with the roadmap for the implementation of the Strategy for the development of small and medium-sized enterprises in Russia until 2030, approved by the government.
It provides for the preparation of a draft law on a comprehensive list of documents that customers have the right to require as part of the application from participants in the procurement - small and medium-sized enterprises.
As well as a list of requirements for these documents.
To date, the law "On the procurement of goods, works, services by individual types of legal entities" framework regulates the procurement activities of individual types of legal entities.
The requirements for the content, form, form and composition of the application for participation in the procurement are established by the customers themselves in the procurement documentation.
"As a result, the customers establish excessive requirements for the content, registration of the application, the compulsory presence of certificates, certificates, extracts, the period of receipt of which in authorized bodies can be compared with the deadline for submitting applications, which leads to the impossibility of participation in such purchase and reduction of quantities".
The new draft law provides for the establishment of a comprehensive list of documents that customers are entitled to require in the form of an application from procurement participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises.
"The adoption of the document will allow to exclude the arbitrary establishment by customers of requirements for the composition and content of applications of participants who are subjects of small and medium-sized enterprises," the explanatory note reads.
