The authorities of Moscow told about the fate of closed landfills
In Sub-Moscow, landfills of solid household waste continue to be closed.
This year, the authorities are promising to eliminate the latter.
Some of the 39 existing landfills are being upgraded to modern waste recycling complexes.
But this option is not possible for every landfill - many of them are covered with dense residential construction.
After the landfill is closed, it stands for re-cultivation - the body of the landfill oversleeps with soil, degassing and filtration systems are installed.
This allows you to stop the chemical processes inside the landfill, so that it does not ignite, does not spill malaria, does not poison the soil and groundwater.
And then the former landfill remains to rise in a useless pile among its surrounding residential building.
Why not make something useful out of it?
For example, in Ruza, where the re-cultivation of the Annino field was completed literally the other day, the authorities are considering an option to make a pile of ski slopes.
This landfill, which operated from 1976 to 2016, grew so much that it went beyond the boundaries of the land allocated to it.
Therefore, during the re-cultivation it was necessary to buy the neighboring plots, de facto already long stuffed with garbage under the rubbish.
"Sometime will pass, the landing ground will "send", the forts will be built, and we will think what can be done to make it begin to benefit.
Directly in the eye - the ski resort," - said the head of the Ruz district Nikolay Parthenov to journalists.
